---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Foil Engine | pbrain studios" description="AI-powered NPC conversation platform. State machines meet language models.">

<div
  class="fixed top-0 -z-10 !w-screen md:block h-screen bg-cover bg-center tracking-wide"
></div>

<section
  class="min-h-0 flex-1 !z-[20] relative w-full flex flex-col items-center justify-center pt-8 pb-10 overflow-auto"
  id="hero"
>
  <div class="w-full max-w-4xl px-6 md:px-10 flex flex-col gap-10 text-zinc-800 leading-relaxed">

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="text-center">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold mb-3">Foil Engine</h1>
      <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-zinc-600">
        AI-powered NPC conversation platform where state machines meet language models.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Hero Image -->
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-zinc-300 overflow-hidden">
      <img
        src="/foil-engine-editor.png"
        alt="Foil Engine editor showing state machine diagram and chat preview"
        class="w-full object-cover"
        loading="eager"
      />
    </div>

    <!-- Overview -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 text-base md:text-lg">
      <p>
        Foil Engine is a developer platform for building interactive NPCs without scripted
        dialogue trees. You define character personas and model conversations as state machines.
        The AI generates natural language responses while following your defined flow, keeping
        characters in persona across multi-turn conversations.
      </p>
      <p>
        The system separates concerns cleanly: personas define who the character is, scenarios
        define conversation structure, states define phases, and transitions define the rules
        that move between them. Each interaction is evaluated by the AI as one of four decisions
        (pass, redirect, reject, or kick out), creating structured yet dynamic conversations.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Key Capabilities -->
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Key Capabilities</h2>
      <ul class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 text-zinc-700">
        <li class="border border-zinc-300 rounded-xl p-4">
          <span class="font-semibold block mb-1">State machine conversations</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-zinc-600">Structured flows with AI-evaluated transitions, not free-form chat</span>
        </li>
        <li class="border border-zinc-300 rounded-xl p-4">
          <span class="font-semibold block mb-1">RAG-enhanced knowledge</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-zinc-600">Real-world facts retrieved via Perplexity and filtered through persona context</span>
        </li>
        <li class="border border-zinc-300 rounded-xl p-4">
          <span class="font-semibold block mb-1">Vendor-agnostic multi-model pipeline</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-zinc-600">Configurable models per service (evaluation, response, summarization) via LiteLLM. Swap providers without code changes</span>
        </li>
        <li class="border border-zinc-300 rounded-xl p-4">
          <span class="font-semibold block mb-1">Visual editor</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-zinc-600">Drag-and-drop state machine builder with live chat preview</span>
        </li>
        <li class="border border-zinc-300 rounded-xl p-4">
          <span class="font-semibold block mb-1">Game-ready SDKs</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-zinc-600">Python, TypeScript, and Unity with full type support and async patterns</span>
        </li>
        <li class="border border-zinc-300 rounded-xl p-4">
          <span class="font-semibold block mb-1">Multi-scenario progression</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-zinc-600">Linked conversation machines with cross-scenario variable passing</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Tech Stack -->
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Tech Stack</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm text-zinc-700">
        <div class="border border-zinc-300 rounded-xl p-4">
          <span class="font-semibold block mb-2">Frontend</span>
          <span class="text-zinc-600">Next.js 15, React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS 4, ReactFlow</span>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-zinc-300 rounded-xl p-4">
          <span class="font-semibold block mb-2">Backend</span>
          <span class="text-zinc-600">Python, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy 2.0, Pydantic</span>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-zinc-300 rounded-xl p-4">
          <span class="font-semibold block mb-2">AI & Knowledge</span>
          <span class="text-zinc-600">LiteLLM (vendor-agnostic: OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.), Perplexity sonar-pro (RAG), Pydantic structured outputs</span>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-zinc-300 rounded-xl p-4">
          <span class="font-semibold block mb-2">Infrastructure</span>
          <span class="text-zinc-600">Vercel, Render, Supabase (PostgreSQL, Auth, RLS)</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Origin Story -->
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Origin</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 text-base md:text-lg">
        <p>
          Foil Engine grew out of the dialogue system originally built for
          <a href="https://surpg.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline hover:text-zinc-500 transition">Sexy Unique RPG</a>.
          After shipping an AI-driven game with custom NPC conversations, I extracted the core
          engine and rebuilt it as a standalone platform, complete with a visual editor, REST API, and
          native SDKs for game developers and educators.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CTAs -->
    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 pt-2">
      <a
        href="https://foilengine.io"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
        class="px-5 py-3 rounded-xl bg-[#2d3436] text-white font-medium hover:opacity-90 transition text-center"
      >
        Try the Editor
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://foilengine.io/docs"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
        class="px-5 py-3 rounded-xl border border-zinc-300 text-zinc-800 font-medium hover:border-zinc-500 transition text-center"
      >
        View Docs
      </a>
      <a
        href="/projects"
        class="px-5 py-3 rounded-xl border border-zinc-300 text-zinc-800 font-medium hover:border-zinc-500 transition text-center"
      >
        All Projects
      </a>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

</Layout>
